{
  "stem": "27509.7",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they wanted to take somebody with them who knows-- who knows something about Jewish schools to give them some of-- sort of an idea what it is, and how it is, and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Having been known to them from the management of the kitchen and the hospital, it was a logical thing for them to turn to me and invite me to come with them as part of that investigating [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] of events and we inspect the school.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was very nice school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I had my first lesson in-- in the difference between the concept of European understanding of Judaism and Jewish education and Anglo-Saxon and Jewish education system.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I found the class with the children sitting there with their heads covered, and their teacher with his head covered teaching them about a tree and a-- and a bird, and so on and so forth, a [INAUDIBLE] primer.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I stood there, and I looked, and I just couldn't make it out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And when we walked out, the [INAUDIBLE] was with us-- one of the [INAUDIBLE]-- the-- the-- the Shanghai [INAUDIBLE] was with us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As we walked-- he was a tall, towering man, broad shoulders, 6 foot 2'.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I turned around to him and said, so, whatever his name was, tell me please, why are the children sitting there with their heads covered?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he said, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I said, but they are not learning religion, they are not learning bible.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's learning a secular story about birds and trees.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's not Jewish religion.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The only answer I could give you is that's how it's done in England.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So that was my first lesson.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
